               <p>THOMAS R - sworn. - I am a <rs id="t18021027-113-viclabel624" type="occupation">baker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18021027-113-victim1034 t18021027-113-viclabel624"></join>, and the prisoner was my <rs id="t18021027-113-deflabel625" type="occupation">journeyman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18021027-113-defend1032 t18021027-113-deflabel625"></join>; I observed him with something hid under his coat, searched him, and found several of these loaves, (producing them); and the rest were hid in the bake-house.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. When I went to work with my master, it was agreed I should have a weekly allowance of bread; he having a large quantity of loaves on hand, proposed that he and I should fill baskets, and sell them in St. Giles's at a low price; not doing so, it was to be kept for my use, and it was kept till it became so mouldy I could not eat it, and I made those cakes to eat instead, and not to sell. <rs id="t18021027-113-verdict626" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18021027-113-verdict626" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 48.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18021027-113-punish627" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18021027-113-punish627" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
